window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><i>I know all about being afraid of the dark. Like my uncle, in my thirties I found my way into my own dark forest, face-to-face with the big bad wolf. He was so close to me the whole time, I could taste the blood on his breath. Meeting him felt like a fairytale. In fact, I met him at a bar called the Wolf's Lair. - </i>Blackout, a podcast by Georgia Sansom</p> <p>A sensational trial for an historic serial murder. A podcast that shines a light on how a city became afraid of the dark. A missing woman with a trail of secrets. A top lawyer famous for defending notorious criminals. A retired homicide cop hunting for the truth.</p> <p>Intriguing and distinctive, this taut novella in three interweaving narratives will have you listening with the lights on.</p> <p>This project is a work of fiction. Names, characters, companies and events are either the product of the authorâ€™s imagination or are used fictitiously. Any resemblance to actual persons, living or dead, companies or events is entirely coincidental.</p>"; 
